      "message": "[Critical] Line 362: 🔴 Critical Issues - The congestion signal uses the ponderated loss value, but `pondLoss_` starts at 10.0f. With a first RTCP report showing 0% loss, `getPonderateLoss()` returns 5, which is above the 3% threshold and will reduce video bitrate even on a healthy call. Gate the audio→video QoS callback on actual observed loss, or initialize/use a separate QoS loss accumulator that cannot start above the threshold.\n```suggestion\n    if (rtcpi-\u003epacketLoss \u003e\u003d AUDIO_CONGESTION_THRESHOLD \u0026\u0026 pondLoss \u003e\u003d AUDIO_CONGESTION_THRESHOLD) {\n```",
