      "message": "[Medium] Line 818: 🟡 Suggestions - Audio-triggered reductions update only `lastAudioQosReduction_`; the existing bitrate adaptation state is not told that a decrease just happened. That can let the normal video adaptation path raise the bitrate again immediately on the next RTCP cycle, partially undoing the audio-priority decision. Update the shared decrease/recovery state when applying this reduction so existing cooldown logic is respected.\n```suggestion\n        lastAudioQosReduction_ \u003d now;\n        lastBitrateDecrease \u003d now;\n```",
